{
  "stem": "7455.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 135,
      "text": "She was a dress designer, very glamorous and beautiful, and a sense of humor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 136,
      "text": "And she livened up our summer with singing and joking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 137,
      "text": "We took walks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 138,
      "text": "And when she was leaving, I had tears because there goes that beauty, that romantic idea-- ideas that I had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 139,
      "text": "So she brought that flair of the big city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 140,
      "text": "And she said, you're such a-- she's such a romantic child.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 141,
      "text": "I never forgotten that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 142,
      "text": "We didn't want to drink milk, and my mother wanted us to drink.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 143,
      "text": "So for every gl-- glass of milk, she paid us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 144,
      "text": "So every child had a piggy bank where we-- we drank a glass of milk, she gave us money.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 145,
      "text": "So by the end of summer, we were loaded.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 146,
      "text": "My mother would make preserves st-- from strawberries, from raspberries to bring home for the summer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 147,
      "text": "Those forests were beautiful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 148,
      "text": "It was-- it was good to be alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 149,
      "text": "In 19-- in 1939, when-- in 1941-- in 1939 when the war broke out, we were sitting in a cellar and bombs and machine gunning.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 150,
      "text": "We were afraid-- and artillery.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 151,
      "text": "And troops were passing because Brody, as I said, was a passageway to Russia-- tanks and troops.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And suddenly it was quiet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were all in a cellar-- and all our tenants-- for safety.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father looked out and he saw a neighbor coming towards him running, waving his arms.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Russians are here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We anticipated that the Germans are going to march in in 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were frightened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where do the Russians come in?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Russians-- we did not know that the Russians made a pact with Stalin to set-- to split Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eastern Poland was to be occupied by the Russian troops.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Western Poland will be occupied by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
